com.hazelcast.internal.networking.nio

Class NioEventLoopGroup

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hazelcast.internal.networking.nio.NioEventLoopGroup
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EventLoopGroup

    public class NioEventLoopGroup
extends Object
implements EventLoopGroup
    A non blocking EventLoopGroup implementation that makes use of Selector to have a limited set of io threads, handle an arbitrary number of connections. Each NioChannel has 2 parts:
    1. NioChannelReader: triggered by the NioThread when data is available in the socket. The NioChannelReader takes care of reading data from the socket and calling the appropriate ChannelInboundHandler
    2. NioChannelWriter: triggered by the NioThread when either space is available in the socket for writing, or when there is something that needs to be written e.g. a Packet. The NioChannelWriter takes care of calling the appropriate ChannelOutboundHandler to convert the OutboundFrame to bytes in in the ByteBuffer and writing it to the socket.
    By default the NioThread blocks on the Selector, but it can be put in a 'selectNow' mode that makes it spinning on the selector. This is an experimental feature and will cause the io threads to run hot. For this reason, when this feature is enabled, the number of io threads should be reduced (preferably 1).
